\textbf{Key observation.}
At $M\!\ge\!32$ the BF16 reduction flag produces the same non-zero deviation as
default cuBLAS. Large-$M$ algorithms that satisfy the flag still use BF16 split-K
reduction, so restricting the algorithm set does not by itself force FP32
