Logit perturbation compounds at the model level. On Llama-3.1-8B at $bs\!=\!8$,
$\max|\Delta\text{logit}|\!=\!26.81$, the mean is $2.57$, and 99.8\% of logit
positions are affected (Appendix~\ref{app:logit_error}). \dllm drives all of these
to zero. Log-probabilities are more sensitive than argmax. Even when the top-1
token is stable, $\log P(\text{top-1})$ shifts whenever any logit moves. Only
about 2.4\% of tokens have a top-2 gap below $0.1\nats$ and are vulnerable to
argmax flips, so argmax-based tests understate the severity.

